   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_XXXX_unknown_02_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <salute>
   My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauA1">Alicia</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p> - I beg you will guess who<lb/>
      wrote in a letter to me what follows - I am<lb/>
      not sure that you ever saw the person who wrote it -<lb/>
      "We are busy in this family reading Capt<hi rend="superscript">n</hi>
               <lb/>
      "Beaufort's Karamania and we all not only<lb/>
      "like, but admire it. I never read description so<lb/>
      "clear, and so well given in <del>
                  <unclear>so</unclear>
               </del> such few words<lb/>
      "I have frequently desired my nephew who is<lb/>
      "our reader to read a sentence over again in<lb/>
      "admiration of the many ideas comprised in it<lb/>
      "and the simple and elegant choice of words.<lb/>
      "-It was not without reason that in speaking to<lb/>
      "me of his extreme delicacy in mentioning him<lb/>
      "self in his writings you said "He is qui<unclear/>
               <note>page torn</note>
               <lb/>
      "<hi rend="underline">prud<unclear/>
               </hi>
               <note>page torn</note> in this respect" - We have as ye<unclear/>
               <note>page torn</note>
               <lb/>
      "read only to the middle of the book; he has<lb/>
      "made use of the pronoun <hi rend="underline">I</hi> only on two<lb/>
      "occasions; yet he has contrived to refrain with<lb/>
      "out any affectation &amp; without speaking of him,<lb/>
               "self in the second person a kind of sly modesty<lb/>
      "which I dislike" -</p>
            <lb/>
            <closer>
               <hi rend="underline">Short</hi> &amp; sweet - Yours affectionately<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauH1">Honora</persName> desires her love to you.<lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF1">Capt<hi rend="superscript">n</hi>.. Beaufort. R. N</persName>
                  </addrLine>
